1st lead: Lebanon says Hariri killed by suicide car bomb.
Hariri and eight other people were killed in a huge explosion, which occurred as Hariri's motorcade was passing by in the seafront area of the Lebanese capital Beirut.
He came to office first in 1992 and headed five governments over 12 years.
At least eight others were killed, including some of Hariri's bodyguards.
Security forces sealed off the scene, where a big crater was gouged by the explosion.
